On July 30, 2009, Vice President Biden hosted two conference calls with governors and local officials to discuss the implementation of the Recovery Act. The conference calls included governors Tim Kaine, Linda Lingle, Jack Markell, Bill Richardson, and Mike Rounds, as well as mayors and county executives such as Mark Funkhouser, Melvin "Kip" Holden, Danny Jones, Jim Schmitt, Isiah "Ike" Leggett, and Lee N. May. The purpose of the calls was to discuss the progress of the Recovery Act and its impact at the state and local levels.